         =20

         =20
            <div class=3D"archive__item-excerpt">
              <p><a href=3D"https://root.cern/about/license">Open source</a=
>, which means that you can use it freely and <a href=3D"https://root.cern/=
install/build_from_source">modify it</a>. It adopts an open development pro=
cess, inviting <a href=3D"https://root.cern/contribute">its users to contri=
bute to it</a>.</p>

            </div>
         =20

         =20
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
 =20
    <div class=3D"feature__item">
      <div class=3D"archive__item">
       =20

        <div class=3D"archive__item-body">
         =20
            <h2 class=3D"archive__item-title">$ _</h2>
         =20

         =20
            <div class=3D"archive__item-excerpt">
              <p>Delivered with a <a href=3D"https://root.cern/primer#learn=
-c-at-the-root-prompt">C++ interpreter</a>, ideal for <i>fast prototyping</=
i>. ROOT also offers a Python interface to all its components with <a href=
=3D"https://root.cern/manual/python/">dynamic bindings</a>. <a href=3D"http=
s://nbviewer.jupyter.org/url/root.cern/doc/master/notebooks/rf301_compositi=
on.C.nbconvert.ipynb">Jupyter notebooks are supported too</a>.</p>

            </div>
         =20

         =20
        </div>
      </div>
